<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3502] C++ TServerSocket passes small buffer to getsockname</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3502</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TServerSocket::listen is using a struct sockaddr instead of a struct sockaddr_storage when calling getsockname. It then fails to get the bound port number when the configured port is 0. See the following stackoverflow post:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14624427/wsaefault-error-when-use-getsockname-function&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14624427/wsaefault-error-when-use-getsockname-function&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Microsoft Visual Studio 2015&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12923882">THRIFT-3502</key>
